description:
Will Brinson is joined by Sean Wagner-McGough to react to several news items from around the NFL on New Year's Eve. The guys first discuss John Dorsey parting ways with the Browns (2:50), Doug Marrone being retained by the Jaguars (13:50), more indecision from the Cowboys on Jason Garrett (23:30), J.J. Watt returning for the Texans in the playoffs (34:00), and Ryan Pace confirming Mitchell Trubisky will be the Bears starting QB in 2020 (38:00).
